channel.title: [317]Tom's Cache editor problem
channel.description:
Alright, I'm using Tom's Cache Editor to add the newer login interface on my devolution source. And I get an error when trying to replace a file inside of a .dat file in my cache. Specifically, I'm trying to replace #4 inside of "main_file_cache.idx0" with an "archive4" .dat file. But when I click on #4 inside of main_file_cache.idx0 , it gives me this error.
[code]An error occurred whilst loading archive. com.jagex.cache.util.exceptions.CacheException: Sector cache number didn't match expected cache number.[/code]
Here is a screenshot in case you want one. O_o
[IMG]http://i56.tinypic.com/2wcen2r.jpg[/img]
I also get a 2nd error when trying to open interface.jag on the cache editor.
[IMG]http://i55.tinypic.com/16kxhdc.jpg[/img]
Be specific if you're going to help. [b]I still need help with both errors. Not just one.[/b]
